        <updateDate>2021-01-14T17:51:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p> <b>Collegiate Athlete Compensation Rights Act</b></p> <p>This bill permits student athletes to earn compensation for the use of their name, image, or likeness (NIL) and creates a uniform, national framework for NIL compensation.</p> <p>The bill also (1) prohibits certain activities of institutions, boosters, and third-party licensees relating to athlete classification, scholarships, and contracts; and (2) directs the Federal Trade Commission to oversee all activities and approve all rules issued by a private, independent, and nonprofit entity responsible for developing and administering NIL rules concerning student athletes and specified others.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
